      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SHE'S AN ARTIST (5) probably hasn't quite reached the heights she promised early and she was touched off here last time out at $1.70 but the winner there is a good horse and they beat the rest comfortably. Against her own sex here suits, she gets in with 54kg and gets every hope to atone. GENTLE STEEL (3) stepped up from 955m to 1100m last start at Caulfield and was gifted a very soft lead, making the most of it with a smart win. Down the straight is a new challenge but she's very hard to knock. She had the measure of SHE'S GOT PIZZAZZ (4) there who was first up. She stays at 1100m which is a knock but she'll strip fitter and the straight can suit. BOSSY NIC (2) resumes, she'll get a touch further but can sprint well fresh. POP AWARD (1) struggled fresh in a strange race, second up last time in she did beat Arkansaw Kid which is outstanding form.",
